---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "High School GPA Calculator",
  description: "Calculate your weighted and unweighted GPA instantly. See how AP, IB, and Honors classes impact your college admissions chances.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between weighted and unweighted GPA?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "An unweighted GPA is calculated on a standard 4.0 scale, where an A is 4.0, a B is 3.0, and so on, regardless of the class difficulty. A weighted GPA takes the difficulty of the course into account. Honors classes typically add 0.5 points (an A is 4.5), while Advanced Placement (AP) or International Baccalaureate (IB) classes usually add 1.0 point (an A is 5.0)."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do colleges look at my GPA?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Colleges generally look at both your weighted and unweighted GPA. However, many colleges will recalculate your GPA using their own specific formulas, often removing non-academic classes like physical education or art. They pay close attention to your course rigor (the difficulty of your classes), which is why a slightly lower weighted GPA from taking AP classes might look better than a perfect 4.0 unweighted GPA from taking all easy classes."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do all high schools calculate GPA the same way?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No, high schools use various methods to calculate GPA. Some use a 4.0 scale, while others might use a 5.0, 6.0, or even a 100-point scale. Furthermore, schools differ in how they award extra points for Honors, AP, or IB classes. Always check your specific high school's handbook or speak with your guidance counselor to understand your school's exact GPA calculation method."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a 'good' high school GPA?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A 'good' GPA depends entirely on your college goals. The national average high school GPA is around a 3.0 (a B average). For highly competitive universities (like Ivy League schools), a good GPA is typically a 3.8 to 4.0 unweighted, with a very high weighted GPA showing you took the hardest classes available. For many state universities, a 3.0 to 3.5 is often competitive."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I raise my GPA during my senior year?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, but the impact will be smaller because you already have three years of grades established. The more credits you have, the harder it is to change your cumulative GPA. However, getting excellent grades in your senior year shows an upward trend, which colleges look upon very favorably, even if the overall numerical GPA doesn't jump significantly."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<SiteLayout site="mathtools" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://photonbuilder.com/mathtools/high-school-gpa-calculator" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>High School GPA Calculator</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Calculate both weighted and unweighted GPA based on course difficulty.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="results-panel">
        <div class="result-item">
          <div class="result-label">Unweighted GPA</div>
          <div class="result-value" id="unweighted-res">0.00</div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-item">
          <div class="result-label">Weighted GPA</div>
          <div class="result-value" id="weighted-res">0.00</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="course-header">
        <div>Course Name (Optional)</div>
        <div>Credits</div>
        <div>Grade</div>
        <div>Class Type</div>
        <div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="course-list" id="course-list">
        <!-- Rows injected via JS -->
      </div>

      <button class="btn-add" id="btn-add">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"></line><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line></svg>
        Add Another Course
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>Understanding High School GPA Calculation</h2>
      <p>Your Grade Point Average (GPA) is one of the most critical numbers on your high school transcript. It represents your cumulative academic performance and is a primary factor used by college admissions officers to evaluate your readiness for higher education. There are two main types of GPA: unweighted and weighted.</p>

      <h3>What is Unweighted GPA?</h3>
      <p>The unweighted GPA is the most common and standard way of measuring academic performance. It is measured on a scale of 0.0 to 4.0. In an unweighted system, the difficulty of the course is not taken into consideration. An 'A' in an introductory art class holds the exact same numerical weight as an 'A' in Advanced Placement Calculus.</p>

      <table class="scale-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Letter Grade</th>
            <th>Percentage</th>
            <th>Standard Unweighted GPA</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>A+, A</td><td>93 - 100</td><td>4.0</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A-</td><td>90 - 92</td><td>3.7</td></tr>
          <tr><td>B+</td><td>87 - 89</td><td>3.3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>B</td><td>83 - 86</td><td>3.0</td></tr>
          <tr><td>B-</td><td>80 - 82</td><td>2.7</td></tr>
          <tr><td>C+</td><td>77 - 79</td><td>2.3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>C</td><td>73 - 76</td><td>2.0</td></tr>
          <tr><td>C-</td><td>70 - 72</td><td>1.7</td></tr>
          <tr><td>D+</td><td>67 - 69</td><td>1.3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>D</td><td>65 - 66</td><td>1.0</td></tr>
          <tr><td>F</td><td>Below 65</td><td>0.0</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>What is Weighted GPA?</h3>
      <p>A weighted GPA takes into account the rigor or difficulty of your coursework. Because Honors, AP (Advanced Placement), and IB (International Baccalaureate) classes are more challenging, high schools often assign them extra point values to reward students who take on tougher academic loads. This scale often goes up to 5.0, and sometimes even higher depending on the school district.</p>

      <p>The standard weighting system typically adds points as follows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Regular Classes:</strong> No extra points added (A = 4.0).</li>
        <li><strong>Honors Classes:</strong> Usually adds 0.5 points to the standard scale (A = 4.5).</li>
        <li><strong>AP/IB/College Level Classes:</strong> Usually adds 1.0 point to the standard scale (A = 5.0).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How to Calculate Your GPA (The Formula)</h3>
      <p>To calculate your GPA manually, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Convert Grades to Points:</strong> Using the scale above, convert each letter grade you received into its corresponding decimal GPA value. For a weighted GPA, add the extra 0.5 or 1.0 points to the base value depending on the class type.</li>
        <li><strong>Multiply by Credits:</strong> Multiply the points for each class by the number of credits the class is worth. (Most full-year classes are worth 1.0 credit, while semester classes might be worth 0.5 credits). These are your "Grade Points."</li>
        <li><strong>Sum the Grade Points:</strong> Add all of your Grade Points together.</li>
        <li><strong>Divide by Total Credits:</strong> Divide the total sum of Grade Points by the total number of credits you attempted. The result is your GPA.</li>
      </ol>

      <p><strong>Example Calculation:</strong></p>
      <p>Imagine you took three 1-credit classes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular History: B (3.0 base &times; 1 credit = 3.0 points)</li>
        <li>Honors English: A (4.0 base + 0.5 honors bonus = 4.5 &times; 1 credit = 4.5 points)</li>
        <li>AP Calculus: B (3.0 base + 1.0 AP bonus = 4.0 &times; 1 credit = 4.0 points)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Total Grade Points: 3.0 + 4.5 + 4.0 = 11.5 points.<br>Total Credits: 3.<br>Weighted GPA: 11.5 / 3 = <strong>3.83</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      {schema.mainEntity.map(faq => (
        <details>
          <summary>{faq.name}</summary>
          <p>{faq.acceptedAnswer.text}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const courseList = document.getElementById('course-list');
      const btnAdd = document.getElementById('btn-add');
      const unweightedRes = document.getElementById('unweighted-res');
      const weightedRes = document.getElementById('weighted-res');

      const gradeScale = {
        'A+': 4.0, 'A': 4.0, 'A-': 3.7,
        'B+': 3.3, 'B': 3.0, 'B-': 2.7,
        'C+': 2.3, 'C': 2.0, 'C-': 1.7,
        'D+': 1.3, 'D': 1.0, 'F': 0.0
      };

      const weightScale = {
        'regular': 0.0,
        'honors': 0.5,
        'ap': 1.0
      };

      function createCourseRow() {
        const row = document.createElement('div');
        row.className = 'course-row';

        row.innerHTML = `
          <input type="text" class="course-name" placeholder="e.g. AP History" aria-label="Course Name">
          <input type="number" class="course-credits" value="1.0" min="0.1" step="0.5" aria-label="Credits">
          <select class="course-grade" aria-label="Grade">
            <option value="A+">A+ (97-100)</option>
            <option value="A" selected>A (93-96)</option>
            <option value="A-">A- (90-92)</option>
            <option value="B+">B+ (87-89)</option>
            <option value="B">B (83-86)</option>
            <option value="B-">B- (80-82)</option>
            <option value="C+">C+ (77-79)</option>
            <option value="C">C (73-76)</option>
            <option value="C-">C- (70-72)</option>
            <option value="D+">D+ (67-69)</option>
            <option value="D">D (65-66)</option>
            <option value="F">F (Below 65)</option>
          </select>
          <select class="course-weight" aria-label="Class Type">
            <option value="regular" selected>Regular</option>
            <option value="honors">Honors (+0.5)</option>
            <option value="ap">AP / IB (+1.0)</option>
          </select>
          <button class="btn-remove" aria-label="Remove Course">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
          </button>
        `;

        const inputs = row.querySelectorAll('input, select');
        inputs.forEach(input => {
          input.addEventListener('input', calculateGPA);
          input.addEventListener('change', calculateGPA);
        });

        const removeBtn = row.querySelector('.btn-remove');
        removeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          row.remove();
          calculateGPA();
        });

        return row;
      }

      function calculateGPA() {
        const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.course-row');
        let totalCredits = 0;
        let totalUnweightedPoints = 0;
        let totalWeightedPoints = 0;

        rows.forEach(row => {
          const creditsInput = row.querySelector('.course-credits');
          const gradeSelect = row.querySelector('.course-grade');
          const weightSelect = row.querySelector('.course-weight');

          const credits = parseFloat(creditsInput.value);
          if (isNaN(credits) || credits <= 0) return;

          const grade = gradeSelect.value;
          const weight = weightSelect.value;

          const unweightedPoint = gradeScale[grade];
          const weightedPoint = grade !== 'F' ? unweightedPoint + weightScale[weight] : 0.0;

          totalCredits += credits;
          totalUnweightedPoints += (unweightedPoint * credits);
          totalWeightedPoints += (weightedPoint * credits);
        });

        if (totalCredits > 0) {
          const unweightedGPA = totalUnweightedPoints / totalCredits;
          const weightedGPA = totalWeightedPoints / totalCredits;

          unweightedRes.textContent = unweightedGPA.toFixed(2);
          weightedRes.textContent = weightedGPA.toFixed(2);
        } else {
          unweightedRes.textContent = '0.00';
          weightedRes.textContent = '0.00';
        }
      }

      btnAdd.addEventListener('click', () => {
        courseList.appendChild(createCourseRow());
        calculateGPA();
      });

      // Initialize with 4 default rows
      for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
        courseList.appendChild(createCourseRow());
      }
      calculateGPA();
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }

    .calculator-container { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); }

    .results-panel { display: flex; justify-content: space-around; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; }
    .result-item { text-align: center; }
    .result-label { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-primary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .result-value { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); font-family: var(--font-mono); line-height: 1; }

    .course-header { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr 1.5fr auto; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; padding: 0 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .course-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .course-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr 1.5fr auto; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; background: var(--bg-color); padding: 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); transition: border-color 0.2s; }
    .course-row:focus-within { border-color: var(--accent-color); }

    input, select { background: transparent; color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.5rem; border-radius: 6px; width: 100%; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    input:focus, select:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }

    .btn-remove { background: none; border: none; color: #ef4444; font-size: 1.5rem; cursor: pointer; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 32px; height: 32px; border-radius: 4px; transition: background 0.2s; padding: 0; line-height: 1; }
    .btn-remove:hover { background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); }

    .btn-add { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 15%, transparent); color: var(--accent-color); border: 1px dashed var(--accent-color); width: 100%; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
    .btn-add:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 25%, transparent); }

    .explainer { margin: 4rem 0; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer h2 { color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
    .explainer h3 { color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
    .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
    .explainer ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
    .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

    .scale-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .scale-table th, .scale-table td { border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; }
    .scale-table th { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .scale-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--bg-color); }
    .scale-table td { color: var(--text-secondary); }

    .faq-section { margin-top: 4rem; }
    .faq-section h2 { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1.2rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); transition: all 0.2s; }
    .faq-section details[open] { border-color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); list-style-position: inside; }
    .faq-section summary::marker { color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-section details p { margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .course-header { display: none; }
      .course-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; grid-template-areas: "name name" "credits grade" "weight remove"; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem; }
      .course-row input[type="text"] { grid-area: name; }
      .course-row input[type="number"] { grid-area: credits; }
      .course-row select:nth-of-type(1) { grid-area: grade; }
      .course-row select:nth-of-type(2) { grid-area: weight; }
      .course-row .btn-remove { grid-area: remove; justify-self: end; }

      .course-row::before { content: "Credits"; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary); grid-area: credits; transform: translateY(-1.5rem); position: absolute; pointer-events: none; }
      .course-row::after { content: "Grade"; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary); grid-area: grade; transform: translateY(-1.5rem); position: absolute; pointer-events: none; }
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
